summary: Oddly enough, my favorite scene in Spider-Man Homecoming is the scene where Peter is just helping regular people in the streets...
body: Oddly enough, my favorite scene in Spider-Man Homecoming is the scene where Peter is just helping regular people in the streets of New York. I don’t know, it’s just that after watching all the other heroes just dealing with big catastrophies, it’s refreshing and nice to see someone just helping the normal people. That’s something that I really loved of Sam Raimi’s trilogy, those scenes that showed how Spider-Man cared more of saving the regular people instead of just defeating the bad guy and making jokes *cough Amazing Spider-Man 2* and to see that type of scene make it’s return on Homecoming was something I truly loved and appreciated.

summary: Now, we all thought that the Tony Stark - Peter Parker mentor-ship was a little like this: BUT what if I told you it was a...
body:
Now, we all thought that the Tony Stark - Peter Parker mentor-ship was a little like this:

BUT what if I told you it was a little more like this: 

Now, I know what you’re all thinking. “Who is that broody young man in front of Darth Vader?” And that will be explained if you play The Force Unleashed. The point I’m trying to make is that I believe Tony Stark AKA Tony Stank was training Peter Parker to act as his assassin. 

Where’s the evidence? Well, he built an instant kill mode into his suit. That’s a pretty weird thing to give a teenager. Plus, if you saw Civil War, you’d know that Tony Stark ended up signing the Sokovia Accords, putting him (or rather Iron Man) under the control of the UN, who is the Galatic Empire in this metaphor. This actually never really comes up again, but the important thing is Peter Parker never signed the Accords. He was actually smuggled around by Happy Hogan, using his skills as a chauffeur.  This makes Peter Parker a free superhuman agent, only acting under the instruction of Tony Stark or his subordinates. 

Hence my theory: Tony Stark was specifically training Peter Parker to be his assassin and act where the Sokovia Accords would not allow him to. Now that Tony Stark is dead, and trailer footage of Iron Man 5 Spider-Man Far From Home shows Peter Parker being given access to one of his secret labs, I can only assume Peter Parker will carry out Tony Stark’s terrible plans and enact his legacy.

body:
( Scenarios )

[ Takes place during Endgame ]

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

Y/n and Tony being stuck in space -

Y/n: Tony, I- .. I’m sorry. It must’ve been hard to lose him…

Tony: Kid- .. I know you miss him too. He wasn’t only someone special to me, but to many people. Including you. It’s okay to miss-

Y/n: Mr.Stark forgive me, but you’ll have to excuse me.

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

Hello again, Earth -

As soon as the ship landed and the entrance opened, Y/n was quick to board off. Y/n kept a stern face with her arms around her stomach. She pushed passed everyone quickly heading into the building.

Y/n: I feel like I’m gonna be sick. I need something to eat.

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

@imsmollross

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

Back out there -

Rocket: Alright, who hasn’t been to space before?

….

Rocket: So Ms. Marvel and the hot chick are the only ones who have been out there? Oh boy… Buckle up.

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

Saving her -

Y/n: You’re dead, Maw!

Before Y/n was able to end the life of Ebony Maw, he threw her another direction away from him.

Y/n: NO! YOU BAST-

Peter: Gotcha!

Y/n: *breathless* Thank you. Thank you.

Peter: Can’t die yet! We need you here!

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

[ BONUS ]

Peter: Ned, I just wanted to say, thank you for being my friend.

Ned: OKay…? What’s going on with you? DUDE, who’s that?

Peter: Who?

Ned: There! Outside!

…

Peter instantly recognized the girl standing outside the front entrance.

Peter: She’s here.

Ned: Yo, she looks very familiar! You know her, Pete?

Peter: H- Hey Ned, I’ll- I’ll talk to you later.

Peter quickly jogged his way to the front doors. It’s been a while since the last time he saw Y/n. You can say he was a little too excited.

Peter: Y/n! Hey!

Y/n: Peter. I’m here to say goodbye.

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

┝━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━┥

𝐒𝐨, 𝐒𝐩𝐢𝐝𝐞𝐫-𝐌𝐚𝐧: 𝐅𝐚𝐫 𝐅𝐫𝐨𝐦 𝐇𝐨𝐦𝐞 ,𝐚𝐲𝐞?

𝐓𝐡𝐢𝐬 𝐢𝐬 𝙣𝙤𝙩 𝐭𝐡𝐞 𝐞𝐧𝐝

body:
Repeat after me

Spider-Man is not and should never be treated as “the new Iron Man”

I really hope they have an “who am I? I’m Spider-Man” moment in FFH. Something like at the end of the movie the cops tell him something like “well kid. It seems like you really are the new Iron Man” and Peter just tells them: “no. I’m just your friendly neighborhood Spider-Man”

I don’t know. It just feels so wrong that even Peter says he wants to be “the new Iron Man”
